---
// Privacy — one page. Mad short, per Tres.
// Deliberately untracked: the page about data collection collects none.
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, viewport-fit=cover" />
    <meta name="robots" content="noindex" />
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#101010" />
    <title>Privacy — Tres.</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <!-- sync, pre-paint: sets data-theme before any stylesheet lands -->
    <script is:inline src="/theme.js"></script>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Space+Mono:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/cursor.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <h1>Privacy</h1>
      <p>I collect some visit data. It's anonymous — I don't know who you are
      and don't want to.</p>
      <p>I use it to see what's working and make my sites better. One of the
      tools (Microsoft Clarity) sets cookies to do that.</p>
      <p>A random name (something like <i>ochre-heron-42</i>, stored in your
      browser) groups your visits together so I can tell returning visitors
      from new ones. The name is random — it isn't derived from you or
      anything about you.</p>
      <p>Don't love it? An ad-blocker or your browser's tracking protection
      opts you out just fine, and clearing site data forgets the random
      name. Nothing here keys off your IP.</p>
      <p><a href="/">← back</a> · <a href="mailto:tres@tres.studio">questions</a></p>
    </main>

    <style is:inline>
      :root {
        --paper: #FAFAF7; --ink: #101010;
        --soft: rgba(16,16,16,0.66);      /* secondary text */
        --faint: rgba(16,16,16,0.62);    /* labels, meta   */
        --hair: rgba(0,0,0,0.14);        /* hairlines      */
        --tint: rgba(16,16,16,0.04);     /* image wells    */
      }
      html[data-theme="dark"] {
        --paper: #101010; --ink: #FAFAF7;
        --soft: rgba(250,250,247,0.62);
        --faint: rgba(250,250,247,0.55);
        --hair: rgba(255,255,255,0.16);
        --tint: rgba(250,250,247,0.05);
      }
      html[data-theme="red"] {
        --paper: #E0301F; --ink: #0A0A0A;
        --soft: rgba(10,10,10,0.78);
        --faint: rgba(10,10,10,0.72);
        --hair: rgba(0,0,0,0.25);
        --tint: rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
      }
      html { background: var(--paper); }
      body { color: var(--ink); }
      ::selection { background: var(--ink); color: var(--paper); }

      * { margin: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
      body { font-family: 'Space Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; }
      main { max-width: 52ch; margin: 0 auto; padding: 22vh 24px 20vh; }
      h1 { font-size: 15px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.2em; }
      p { font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.9; margin-top: 1.6em; }
      a { color: inherit; }
      a:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid var(--ink); outline-offset: 3px; }
    </style>
  </body>
</html>
